      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "ELECTRICUTE (11) kicked off his career with a second to the subsequent Group 1 placegetter Gocciadoro at this circuit and distance and has been tackling the good juveniles since, finishing fifth in both the Nutrien Classic Sales Series final and the Bathurst Gold Crown. Draws on the back row but will enjoy the class drop. CAPTAINS BANDIT (2) turned in a much better effort at his latest appearance, finishing third at this circuit and distance. Draws well again and has upside. ESTELLA HERGE (8) draws wide but has finished fourth in stronger races at her last couple so is better placed in maiden company. SHES PRETTY LOU (4) lines up for the first time. By Sweet Lou and hails from the Prest stable. Has been showing ability at the trials and should enjoy a nice run from this favourable starting position. DARKOUTSIDER (6) will enjoy getting back to maiden grade having finished a 1.1m second at that level here two back.",
